The paper discusses the intersection of media and journalism with technology, specifically the Internet and mobile communication. It proposes a strategic alliance between network manufacturers, network operators, and journalism to create a new industry with new actors. This suggests a focus on cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the role of mobile devices and communities, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the need for ethical and philosophical discussions, which could relate to cryptography (cs.CR).
